PrecisAmendment (SCHEDULE No. 990) to the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS which sets a maximum limit on any residual amount of the herbicide "TRICLOPYR" and its metabolites that can be detected in the kidney or liver of cattle, goats, hogs, horses and sheep (0.5 ppm).
